reviews.review_text:
You Can't Go Wrong You can't go wrong streaming a Kevin Tobin matrix.

This is a very pleasant rendition of a well-played show.

I give these shows 5 stars because all the professional elements are extant in the presentation even though it wasn't a barn burner. If this show was a barn burner than I would award it something like 10 out of 5 stars, or some other such nonsensical numeric rating way that drives the purists crazy.

Comic Book Colors.... *Whew*

An A+ recording of a "B-" show.

Still...  A great addition to any collection.

For those of you...  Well, capture it before it disappears.    ;-)

Off and Running What a terrific start to one of the signature years in  Grateful Dead history.

The Last Time bustout is great and fun and all that, but they really shift gears with Cassidy > Deal. Wow.

Then comes a monster of a second set with a huge, epic, Wharf Rat. One for the ages. So good.

Cheers to 1990!
No, more of a C minus. Floppy, unfocused show. Pretty good sound. Glitchy midi-synths pierce the air...
